[A "Pig Progress" interactive map presenting locations of lab-confirmed ASF in wild boar in western Poland (eastern and western clusters) and in eastern Germany is available at https://www.pigprogress.net/Health/African-Swine-Fever/ASF-Poland/?dossier=35415&widgetid=0.

According to information published by the Brandenburg state on 20 Jan 2021, following the confirmation of 30 new cases of infection in wild boar, the accumulated number of ASF-confirmed cases has risen to 527; adding Saxony's 19 cases, the total number for Germany becomes 546 infected wild boar since the start of the epizootic in Germany in early September 2019 when ASF virus was introduced from western Poland.

So far, ASF virus has not been reported from domestic pig farms in Germany. - Mod.AS

